      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Preserve aborted sessions across restart opt-in",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Fixes Gateway restart continuity for aborted fresh main sessions when `session.restartContinuation` is enabled.\n- Preserves the existing `sessionId` when the terminal transcript is newer than the session registry entry, avoiding a new JSONL transcript for the same deterministic main session key.\n- Adds the config schema, user-facing label/help metadata, and regression coverage for the opt-in setting.\n- Intentionally keeps the default behavior unchanged unless `session.restartContinuation` is set to `true`.\n\n## Linked context\n\nFixes #94458\n\nRelated context: #51917\n\nThis was not requested by a maintainer or owner.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: A fresh main session marked `abortedLastRun` after a Gateway restart should continue with the existing session id when `session.restartContinuation=true`, even when the transcript mtime is newer than the registry `updatedAt`.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on Windows, Node.js v24.15.0, running the patched production `initSessionState` entrypoint against actual temporary `sessions.json` and JSONL transcript files.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `node --import tsx ..\\..\\proof\\restart-continuation-proof.mjs`\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output): Copied live terminal output from the production-code proof run:\n\n```text\nOpenClaw restart continuation real behavior proof\n{\n  \"node\": \"v24.15.0\",\n  \"sourceRoot\": \"<local-openclaw-checkout>\",\n  \"tempRoot\": \"<redacted-temp-proof-root>\",\n  \"storePath\": \"<redacted-temp-proof-root>/sessions/sessions.json\",\n  \"transcriptPath\": \"<redacted-temp-proof-root>/sessions/restart-continuation-live-old.jsonl\",\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n  \"restartContinuation\": true,\n  \"existingSessionId\": \"restart-continuation-live-old\",\n  \"transcriptMtimeMs\": 1781784457704,\n  \"registryUpdatedAtMs\": 1781784447704,\n  \"transcriptMtimeNewerThanRegistry\": true,\n  \"initSessionState\": {\n    \"isNewSession\": false,\n    \"sessionId\": \"restart-continuation-live-old\"\n  },\n  \"persistedEntry\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"restart-continuation-live-old\",\n    \"sessionFile\": \"<redacted-temp-proof-root>\\\\sessions\\\\restart-continuation-live-old.jsonl\",\n    \"abortedLastRun\": true,\n    \"endedAt\": 1781784446704\n  },\n  \"checks\": {\n    \"reusedExistingSessionId\": true,\n    \"persistedSessionIdUnchanged\": true,\n    \"noNewSessionCreated\": true\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: The proof hit the transcript-mtime-newer-than-registry condition and `initSessionState` returned `isNewSession=false` with `sessionId=restart-continuation-live-old`; the persisted session store kept the same session id and `abortedLastRun=true`.\n- What was not tested: No additional gaps for the Gateway session-selection behavior covered by this patch. Discord transport delivery and the external lossless-claw package were not run in this local proof.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: The proof uses actual OpenClaw session files and production session initialization logic, but isolates the scenario to Gateway session continuity instead of running an external chat provider or context-engine process.\n- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): The regression test added in this PR captures the previous behavior: without the new continuation path, this same aborted main-session setup was treated as a new session.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/session.test.ts`\n  - Result: 1 file passed, 115 tests passed.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/config/schema.help.quality.test.ts src/config/schema.base.generated.test.ts`\n  - Result: 2 files passed, 29 tests passed.\n- `node --import tsx ..\\..\\proof\\restart-continuation-proof.mjs`\n  - Result: production `initSessionState` reused the existing session id under the restart-continuation condition.\n\nRegression coverage added:\n\n- A new `initSessionState` regression test covers an aborted main session with a transcript mtime newer than registry `updatedAt` and `session.restartContinuation=true`.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes, but only for users who opt in with `session.restartContinuation=true`.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes, a new optional boolean config field was added. Existing configs keep the same default behavior.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nNo.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n\nSession lifecycle reuse for terminal main-session rows after process shutdown.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n\nThe reuse path is gated behind `session.restartContinuation===true`, requires `entry.abortedLastRun===true`, requires a fresh reusable entry, and only bypasses the transcript-mtime-newer-than-registry rotation condition for that restart-continuation case.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n\nGitHub Actions should re-run the Real behavior proof check after this PR body update, then the remaining queued checks and ClawSweeper review should be monitored.\n\nWhat is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?\n\nWaiting on GitHub Actions and ClawSweeper. The external proof section has now been supplied in the PR body.\n\nWhich bot or reviewer comments were addressed?\n\nAddressed the `Real behavior proof` failure and `triage: needs-real-behavior-proof` label by adding the required real behavior proof section with copied live terminal output.\n",
